# SEO Page Rules

Every public-facing `page.tsx` in the `app/` directory must follow these conventions.

## Required Exports

1. **`generateMetadata`** (or static `metadata`) must be exported.
2. Metadata must include a **canonical URL** via `alternates.canonical`.
3. Metadata must include **Open Graph** tags (`title`, `description`, `url`, `siteName`).

## Use the SEO Utility Layer

- Import `buildPageMetadata` from `@/lib/seo` for detail pages.
- Import `buildListingMetadata` from `@/lib/seo` for category/listing pages.
- Do NOT hardcode `https://clip.art` in metadata — use the `path` parameter and let the builder construct the full URL.
- Do NOT manually interpolate title suffixes like `| clip.art` — the builder handles this.

## Title Rules

- Titles must be under 60 characters.
- Use `buildTitle()` (called internally by `buildPageMetadata`) to avoid the "Free Free" duplication bug.
- Pattern: `{Subject} — Free {Category} {ContentType Label} | clip.art`

## JSON-LD Structured Data

- Image detail pages: include `ImageObject` + `BreadcrumbList` via `buildImageJsonLd()` and `buildDetailBreadcrumb()` from `@/lib/seo-jsonld`.
- Video/learn pages: include `VideoObject` via `buildVideoJsonLd()` — only include optional fields when they have values.

## H1 Tag

- Every public page must render exactly one `<h1>` tag.
- The `<h1>` must be in the initial server-rendered HTML (not behind client-side state).

## Sitemap

- After creating a new public page, add it to `app/sitemap.ts`.

## Content Type Paths

When setting the `path` parameter:
- Clip art: `{category}/{slug}`
- Coloring: `coloring-pages/{theme}/{slug}`
- Illustrations: `illustrations/{category}/{slug}`
- Learn: `learn/{slug}`
